                                            <footer class="notes"><h2 data-aid="138546138" id="notetitle1">Notes</h2><ol class="decimal" data-type="marker" start="1"><li class="footnote" id="note1-"><span class="label">1. </span><p data-aid="138546139" id="note1_p1">See general conference messages online at LDS.org and on the Gospel Library app. They will be printed in the <em>Ensign</em> and <em>Liahona.</em> The Church magazines, including the <em>New Era</em> and the <em>Friend,</em> delivered through the mail or downloaded online, are an important part of your home-centered gospel curriculum.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note2-"><span class="label">2. </span><p data-aid="138546140" id="note2_p1">See, for example, <a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/ot/ex/28.html" href="/scriptures/ot/ex/28?lang=eng">Exodus 28</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/ot/ex/29.html" href="/scriptures/ot/ex/29?lang=eng">29</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/ot/lev/8.html" href="/scriptures/ot/lev/8?lang=eng">Leviticus 8</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note3-"><span class="label">3. </span><p data-aid="138546141" id="note3_p1">See <a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.html?verse=29#p29" href="/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.29?lang=eng#p29">Mosiah 4:29</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note4-"><span class="label">4. </span><p data-aid="138546142" id="note4_p1">See Wilford Woodruff, “The Law of Adoption,” discourse delivered at the general conference of the Church, Apr. 8, 1894. President Woodruff said: “We have not got through [with] revelation. We have not got through [with] the work of God. … There will be no end to this work until it is perfected” (<em>Deseret Evening News,</em> Apr. 14, 1894, 9).</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note5-"><span class="label">5. </span><p data-aid="138546143" id="note5_p1"><em>Teachings of Presidents of the Church: Joseph Smith</em> (2007), 142.</p></li></ol></footer>
